title: Kylie Jenner swaps NYFW for date with beau Tyga in NYC | Daily Mail Online
text: Buy now The youngest of the Kardashian-Jenner clan kept her hair sleek and straight and sported glowing face make-up alongside a smoky eye, to accentuate her pretty features. Meanwhile her boyfriend Tyga ensured all eyes were kept on his girl by opting for a more casual jeans, patterned with vibrant paint markings all over. He paired the strides with a bold leather jacket, styled like a racing car driver's, and comfortable black trainers as he followed closely behind his girl to their intimate dinner. Dare to bare: Kylie paired the coat with nude suede knee-high boots, complete with stiletto heel to lengthen her already leggy frame The pair first publicly acknowledged they were together in 2015 after Kylie turned 18 - but they were rumoured to be a couple since 2014. Proving they are stronger than ever, the pair recently enjoyed a holiday together in Costa Rica with Kylie's family, where they shared a number of loved-up selfies and videos with fans. Despite putting on a united front two years later, the relationship has not been without its share of difficulty - having endured a brief split last May. Gorgeous: She kept her hair sleek and straight and sported glowing face make-up alongside a smoky eye, to accentuate her pretty features The reality star admitted to Complex that the relationship has always faced scrutiny - but the pair have learned to overcome the pressures of being an item in the public eye. She explained: 'The first year we started hanging out, everyone around him told him not to be with me.' 'In fact, I still get comments like: "Don’t be with him." But we’re not doing it for the public - we love each other. 'We need to be together at all times. We never get mad at each other, we just figure things out.' Low-key: Meanwhile her boyfriend Tyga ensured all eyes were kept on his girl by opting for a more casual jeans, patterned with vibrant paint markings all over Relaxed: Kylie appeared to be enjoying a relaxing evening with her boyfriend of two years, after a busy week attending numerous NYFW shows, including Jeremy Scott (above) It was reported earlier this week that Kylie is set to star in the music video for her beau's collaboration with Kanye West - alongside her sister Kim Kardashian. According to Us Weekly , she and the 36-year-old, who is married to Kanye, are set to front the video for the rappers' duet 'Feel Me' - with filming already taking place. Sources claimed to the site that Kim filmed her part for the video in New York last month, while things are still quiet about the rest of the family's roles. Adding further fuel to the fire, Kylie and Tyga were then seen heading to the studio together on Thursday - with the Keeping Up With the Kardashians star teasing fans by revealing on Snapchat during the outing: 'Working on a lil somethin!'
